Feedback: Because it was the first scenario, and it was new for me, at first I didnt totally trust on the system but after a while it became easier to not to check everything after I answer each question and when I heard the alert at first I didnt understand what's going on but I knew that I have to do something but when I saw the cars I think that was a little late and I needed to change the line sooner than that.
This time it was easier. Only because the weather was not as clear as the previous te again i felt i need to check the serrounding a little.

The first time that there was a car in my lane, I didnt hear the sound to taking over but I was not sure whether it is better to wait for that or it is better to take action ASAP so I tried to not to  wait for that. I told myself that it is better to change the lane and not to wait for the sound but the second time if there wasnt the alert i didnt understand that i need to change my lane.

It wasnt annoying but this timw i feel confident to put the speed on 120 and when i heard the alert it was too late on that speed to take action. I prefered to hear it a little sooner becaus my speed was higher this time and I was sure that I would here the sound when it is necessary to do sething but I think it was a little late for my speed.

First, I cannot remmeber now what the alerts said on the screen. I only recall beep sound with some text. There were two attentions I needed to pay for - a road closure and a car speeding up in the right. I am not even sure which one the alertbwas targeting to. So I think it might better if there were alert/flashing light on the right mirror too.

I think wording like "potential take-over" popping up on console screen is not the best way to prompt thebdriver. For times like this that requires me to instantly brake, the last thing I would ever want to do is getting distracted from the front view. Better if the sound was designed in a unique way that the driver learns it once and understand that every time it requirew take-overs.

I personally am a kind of person who would be more aware of what could happen every time I see a big/high truck/vehicle. So, I was guessing something might happen when I saw the vehicle far away and was ready to take control before the alert came up. However, the way the alert sounds was not thay annoying and quite helpful in this case though.

The text showing up when alerting could be better. I dont remember exactly but it kinda said something generic. I believe the detection system could have detected that a car was pulling off from the right, so the text could be improved to something like "attention on the front right" or "a car pulling off from the right"
I think the timing of the allert should be a bit earlier and instad of saying be vigilant maybe saying something is ahead and pay attention.
The alert was given too late giving me almost no time to take action.
The alert system was not helping this time. Maybe I took actiob earlier so I was more vigilant myself beforehand.
This time the alerts were more understanable for me and easier and i could take action better. Again the title of allerts could be different. Something like a block ahead.

I would have preferred the alert came a little earlier. The timing was sufticient for a takeover but it still rattled me a bit, I think if I was alerted we earlier I would have had more time to readjust and take assume control.
Satisfied
Much more satisfied but the alert could be more descriptive. Maybe accompanied by a voice that says "take over".
Great. Least demanding of all.
